ivardefs.name: code
ivardefs.desc: A symbol in syntax defined by the system. The symbol may be a predefined code or an expression in a syntax defined by the coding system (e.g. post-coordination).

ivardefs.name: display
ivardefs.desc: A representation of the meaning of the code in the system, following the rules of the system.

ivardefs.name: system
ivardefs.desc: The identification of the code system that defines the meaning of the symbol in the code.

ivardefs.name: userSelected
ivardefs.desc: Indicates that this coding was chosen by a user directly - i.e. off a pick list of available items (codes or displays).

ivardefs.name: version
ivardefs.desc: The version of the code system which was used when choosing this code. Note that a well-maintained code system does not need the version reported, because the meaning of codes is consistent across versions. However this cannot consistently be assured. and
